post_text: Looks like a resource for food and possible financial
shared_text:
The Salvation Army Bath-Brunswick
March 25 at 10:07 AM ·

ATTENTION COMMUNITY in Arrowsic, Bailey Island, Bath, Bowdoin, Bowdoinham, Brunswick, Cundy’s Harbor, Five Islands, Georgetown, Harpswell, Orrs Island, Pejepscot, Phippsburg, Small Point, South Harpswell, Topsham, West Bath, and Woolwich.

Going forward during these time of COVID-19, we have made these changes and want you to be aware of them.

ALL services are by telephone only. This includes financial assistance for housing/rent, heating, and utilities; and our food pantry.

If you are in need of a food box, please call us.

Food baskets will be left outside our front door for you to pick up.

The same procedure for FREE Table items, but you will need to call ahead to see what we have on hand at the time of your call.

Our phone number is (207) 443-3611. We are open 9AM - 2PM, Monday-Thursday.

We will start our 'bagged breakfast/lunch' program Tuesday June 25th. This is just a 'sample' of a lunch..they will change weekly. If you are a student, you can come to 807 Middle Street between 12-1 every Tuesday and Thursday. You can stay for a hot meal and TAKE a bagged lunch/breakfast...or JUST take a bagged lunch/breakfast with you...we will be closed July 4th.
